<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ache2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ache,</orth> vb. (in O. Edd. <emph>ake,</emph> and rhyming to <emph>brake</emph> and <cit><quote>sake,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven ven" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 875</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 58</bibl>), to pain, to smart: <cit><quote>whose swelling dugs do a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven ven" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 875</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>doth make the wound a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1116</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.92" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 4, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 146</bibl>. With <emph>at</emph>: <cit><quote>my wounds a. at you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 96</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the sense --s at thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 69</bibl></cit>.
